  "texts": [
    "The reward structure penalizes collisions and rewards actions leading to safe configurations, with the reward calculation factoring in execution time for collision checking and the diversity of movement strategies.Given that the action space of the agent is multi-discrete in the CD case study and discrete in the 6-DOF case study and based on table 5.3, A2C [121] and PPO [122] RL algorithms are selected since they are suitable for both types of action spaces.",
    "This allows us to maintain consistency across the two case studies.",
    "For both the A2C and PPO algorithms, we have configured number of steps-which is the number of experiences collected from a single environment under the current policy before the next update-to 128 to balance computational efficiency and learning stability.",
    "This parameter choice dictates the batch size indirectly by specifying the count of steps per environment before each policy update.",
    "PPO uses a learning rate of 3 × 10 -4 and A2C uses 7 × 10 -4, both default values known to provide stable learning."
  ],
